z_{n+1} \approx z_n \sim z
n \to \infty
z = \frac12 \left (z + \frac{C}{z} \right ) 
\;C,z>0\;
z_1=\frac12\left(z+\frac Cz\right)\;\;,\;\;z_2=\frac12\left(z_1+\frac C{z_1}\right)\;,\;\;\ldots,\;\;z_n=\frac12\left(z_{n-1}+\frac C{z_{n-1}}\right),\ldots
\alpha=\frac12\left(\alpha+\frac C\alpha\right)\implies\alpha^2=C\implies \alpha=\sqrt C
